  "instructions": [
    "preheat the oven to 375 degrees fahrenheit",
    "mix together the flour, fennel seeds, black pepper, and salt in a large bowl",
    "add the sterbottensost cheese to the flour mixture and stir until well combined",
    "add the butter, eggs, heavy cream, water, parmesan cheese, sour cream, thyme, lemon zest, garlic powder, onion powder, walnuts, carrot, bacon, caramelized onions, parsley, chives, ras el hanout spice blend, cayenne pepper, black cardamom, ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg, coriander, turmeric, and paprika to the cheese mixture and stir until smooth",
    "transfer the mixture to a greased 9x13-inch baking dish and smooth the top",
    "dot the top of the mixture with the melted butter",
    "bake the mixture for 45 minutes, or until it is golden brown and set",
    "remove the mixture from the oven and let it cool for 10 minutes",
    "serve the mixture warm, garnished with chopped fresh herbs and a sprinkle of parmesan cheese",
    "note: this recipe is best served as a side dish or as part of a larger meal, as it is quite rich and filling"
  ],
